data.text:
Good ambience and good food but is it a burger if you cant eat it like a burger?
This review is purely based on what I ordered, which was the burger. No doubt, it was delicious. Double patty and juicy. But it fell apart as soon i took the first bite. Maybe a bit too juicy?
I don't mind a burger falling apart, as long as its served on a plate. Which it was not. It was served on a wooden platter. (?), barely the width of the burger itself. So, I had to ask for an extra plate to catch all the bits.

This aside, the place is great. Good food options and a great drinks menu. With ample onsite parking, this is a great choice if you are in Wilmslow.

data.text:
We visited on a Sunday at around 4pm.
My partner and I thought we would take his mum and gran for some food, glad we did. The service was fantastic, so friendly and welcoming. We ordered 4 main meals. 2 of the steak burgers, 1 pie oh my, and a chicken roast for myself. We really enjoyed them, so full of flavour and beautifully presented. I then ordered the brownie... Wow! I don't have a clue how I fit it all in but glad I did, it was amazing. And to top it off, there was a live musician playing, he was fab, just wish I had asked his name.
Overall, with the service, the atmosphere, and the food... 10/10 we would definitely recommend.
Thank you for such a lovely afternoon.
